# CUSTOMER ACQUISITION COST (CAC) CALCULATOR
# Complete CAC Analysis & Optimization Tool for Indian Startups

## OVERVIEW & DEFINITIONS

### What is Customer Acquisition Cost (CAC)?
CAC = Total Sales & Marketing Expenses / Number of New Customers Acquired

### Why CAC Matters
- Determines profitability of marketing channels
- Helps optimize marketing spend allocation  
- Critical metric for fundraising and valuation
- Guides pricing and business model decisions
- Indicates business scalability

### Target CAC Benchmarks (Industry Averages)
- B2B SaaS: ₹8,000-₹25,000
- E-commerce: ₹800-₹3,000
- Mobile Apps: ₹200-₹1,500
- Professional Services: ₹5,000-₹15,000
- Consumer Products: ₹500-₹2,500

